  <compounddef id="SGN" kind="page">
    <compoundname>SGN</compoundname>
    <title>SGN Function</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">SGN(integer-expression)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Returns the <bold>sign</bold> of an integer expression:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><computeroutput>-1</computeroutput> if the expression is negative</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>0</computeroutput> if the expression is zero</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>1</computeroutput> if the expression is positive</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<sect3 id="SGN_1autotoc_md395">
<title>Examples</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>SGN(-42)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>-1</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>SGN(0)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>0</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>SGN(1234)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>1</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">REM<sp/>Use<sp/>SGN<sp/>in<sp/>a<sp/>comparison</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">balance<sp/>=<sp/>-150</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">IF<sp/>SGN(balance)<sp/>=<sp/>-1<sp/>THEN</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/>PRINT<sp/>&quot;Account<sp/>overdrawn!&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">ENDIF</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="SGN_1autotoc_md397">
<title>Notes</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Input must be an integer expression.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Return value is always <computeroutput>-1</computeroutput>, <computeroutput>0</computeroutput>, or <computeroutput>1</computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Can be used in compact conditionals or arithmetic to simplify sign handling.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
